# Comprehensive Gitignore (Whitelist Strategy)

# 1. Ignore Everything by Default
*

# 2. Whitelist Directories (Recursive)
!*/
!cmd/**
!docs/**
!examples/**
!morphsh/**
!pkg/**
!stdlib/**
!n1/**
!.morph.vz/checksums/**
!.vzoel.jules/**

# 3. Whitelist Root Files
!AGENTS.md
!DESIGN.md
!README.md
!ROADMAP.md
!MEMORY_*.md
!N0_*.md
!N1_*.md
!checksum_gen.go
!go.mod
!go.sum
!.gitignore

# 4. Whitelist Github Workflows (if any)
!.github/**

# 5. Explicitly Ignore Artifacts (Even inside whitelisted directories)
morph
*.exe
*.o
*.a
*.so
*.dylib
*.test
out.c
*_out.c

# Ignore Generated C/H files in examples/ and root but keep .fox files
examples/*.c
examples/*.h
examples/function_type_test
examples/stress_test

# Ignore compiled binaries in n1/ but keep source files (.fox, .c)
n1/checker_core
n1/checker_v2
n1/checker_integrated
n1/regression_simple
n1/std_array
n1/std_map
n1/std_string
n1/symtab_id
n1/test_*
n1/transpiler_asm_simple
!n1/*.fox
!n1/*.c
